        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Provide RGB color annotation — stores the mean color of text pixels in a bounding box as JSON-encoded RGB. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Text annotation for color formatting. \par \b Input\/ \:  RGB float values (red, green, blue). \par \b Output\/ \:  ColorAnnotation instance with JSON-serialized color value. \par \b Links\/ \:  [INHERITS(9): Annotation] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>red &gt;= 0, green &gt;= 0, blue &gt;= 0</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>value is JSON-encoded OrderedDict with &quot;red&quot;, &quot;green&quot;, &quot;blue&quot; keys \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why store color as JSON string rather than tuple? A: Annotation.value is str-typed; JSON provides a structured yet serializable format. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added semantic markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 10[Color text annotation] =&gt; ColorAnnotation \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
